of the afternoon in bed, practising it.

01:08:39.209 --> 01:08:42.626
Well, it is good to know
that you are in such safe hands.

01:08:43.167 --> 01:08:46.292
But Hunter here has to speak
to you about budgets

01:08:46.376 --> 01:08:49.251
and finances and money.

01:08:49.334 --> 01:08:53.126
You know, you have been
in Mexico for eight months now,

01:08:53.209 --> 01:08:55.542
and we only budgeted, as you know, for 12.

01:08:55.626 --> 01:08:57.001
Oh, shall I get the invoices to check?

01:08:57.084 --> 01:08:58.251
Oh, good Lord.

01:08:59.417 --> 01:09:00.959
Oh, well...

01:09:01.042 --> 01:09:03.001
I see it is still quite early for you.

01:09:03.084 --> 01:09:06.251
Oh, yes. I am acclimatizing myself
to local practices,

01:09:06.334 --> 01:09:08.167
many of them imported
from across the border.

01:09:08.251 --> 01:09:10.251
You know? The border with America?

01:09:11.417 --> 01:09:13.792
Russians don't wear pyjamas.

01:09:13.876 --> 01:09:15.959
Even Stalin doesn't wear a pyjama,

01:09:16.042 --> 01:09:19.334
but I'm sure that before long,
he might very well do, red ones.

01:09:19.626 --> 01:09:22.626
I am used to wearing a Russian nightshirt

01:09:22.709 --> 01:09:25.126
which can be a cast-off daytime shirt.

01:09:25.209 --> 01:09:27.084
It is usually genderless, and usually,

01:09:27.167 --> 01:09:29.959
if you tug it well,
can reach down to your knees

01:09:30.042 --> 01:09:33.251
and even, with some sewing
and some adjustments,

01:09:33.334 --> 01:09:35.167
can be made, when it's really cold,

01:09:35.251 --> 01:09:37.584
to reach down to your ankles.

01:09:38.667 --> 01:09:41.292
Well, we will be going now.

01:09:41.376 --> 01:09:43.417
Hunter can make an appointment with you

01:09:43.501 --> 01:09:46.459
to talk finances and... and rushes.

01:09:46.542 --> 01:09:48.501
Is, is that the right word?

01:09:48.584 --> 01:09:51.084
And maybe you could do it
over dinner, Hunter?

01:09:51.167 --> 01:09:52.376
Is that all right?

01:09:54.792 --> 01:09:56.501
Infantile behaviour.

01:10:05.167 --> 01:10:06.876
- Something else?
- No, thank you, Mercedes.

01:10:06.959 --> 01:10:08.042
<i>Gracias</i>, Mercedes.

01:10:09.001 --> 01:10:10.667
However, Mercedes,

01:10:11.709 --> 01:10:14.917
you could put your naked elbow

01:10:15.001 --> 01:10:19.334
under the shower
to test the water temperature.

01:10:19.417 --> 01:10:20.576
And...

01:10:20.959 --> 01:10:24.417
Perhaps you could warm up
the lavatory seat for me again.

01:10:24.501 --> 01:10:26.167
Take your knickers down,

01:10:26.251 --> 01:10:28.667
sit on the seat the wrong way around,

01:10:28.751 --> 01:10:32.042
take a pee, and wriggle around a bit.

01:10:33.042 --> 01:10:35.709
Do you really want me to translate that?

01:10:55.167 --> 01:10:56.459
Was that wise?

01:10:56.542 --> 01:10:58.751
Wise? Wisdom?

01:11:00.334 --> 01:11:01.417
What is that?

01:11:03.001 --> 01:11:06.042
Learning how to live
with a modicum of happiness

01:11:06.126 --> 01:11:07.667
and no harm to others?

01:11:11.542 --> 01:11:14.917
Freud says that there are five things

01:11:15.001 --> 01:11:17.001
essential to a man's happiness

01:11:17.501 --> 01:11:20.001
and if you can get them all perfectly aligned,

01:11:20.084 --> 01:11:22.209
you are extremely fortunate indeed,

01:11:23.376 --> 01:11:27.792
health, work, money,

01:11:27.876 --> 01:11:30.709
sex, and love.

01:11:32.459 --> 01:11:33.959
I have my health.

01:11:34.459 --> 01:11:36.834
I have unbounded amounts of work.

01:11:38.042 --> 01:11:39.459
Money? As you just heard,

01:11:39.542 --> 01:11:40.917
I have a banker, and he has money.

01:11:41.001 --> 01:11:43.751
It's not mine,
but it's in their bank under my name.

01:11:43.834 --> 01:11:45.084
Sex? Well...

01:11:46.501 --> 01:11:49.792
I'm more than agreeably accounted for there.

01:11:49.876 --> 01:11:51.626
And love.

01:11:51.709 --> 01:11:54.834
I have the love of a centaur.

01:11:54.917 --> 01:11:57.834
Obviously a half a man, half a horse.

01:11:57.917 --> 01:11:58.917
A palomino.

01:11:59.334 --> 01:12:01.792
"A Tennessee Walking Horse.

01:12:01.876 --> 01:12:03.917
"A stud out of an Appaloosa."

01:12:05.084 --> 01:12:09.959
Can you whinny and neigh and snort

01:12:10.042 --> 01:12:12.667
and trample the earth with your hooves?

01:12:14.451 --> 01:12:15.667
I can.

01:12:23.834 --> 01:12:25.084
Stop!

01:12:26.584 --> 01:12:27.917
Stop.

01:13:20.376 --> 01:13:21.417
<i>I am 33,</i>

01:13:22.709 --> 01:13:27.084
<i>the age of Christ and Alexander at death,</i>

01:13:29.751 --> 01:13:33.459
<i>the age St Augustine said
we all go to Heaven.</i>

01:13:37.084 --> 01:13:38.417
It is obvious.

01:13:41.167 --> 01:13:43.292
I had to come to Mexico to go to Heaven.

01:13:47.626 --> 01:13:49.126
You could have found this

01:13:50.792 --> 01:13:54.834
ordinary heaven like most other people at 17.

01:13:55.834 --> 01:13:56.917
I doubt it.

01:13:57.792 --> 01:13:59.292
I doubt it very much.

01:13:59.626 --> 01:14:02.917
<i>I doubt that there are many 17-year-olds</i>

01:14:03.001 --> 01:14:05.292
<i>that found Heaven that very first time.</i>

01:14:06.584 --> 01:14:08.209
<i>I am certain that I would not have.</i>

01:14:08.292 --> 01:14:10.501
<i>I was callow in all ways,</i>

01:14:10.584 --> 01:14:12.584
<i>and it would have been a wasted experience.</i>

01:14:13.251 --> 01:14:15.376
33 is the ideal age,

01:14:15.459 --> 01:14:18.959
old enough to be wise enough to know that 33

01:14:20.334 --> 01:14:22.417
is the probable limit of promise.

01:14:22.584 --> 01:14:24.626
After 33, you can no longer claim

01:14:24.709 --> 01:14:27.417
to be a young person of promise any more.

01:14:31.459 --> 01:14:33.209
And at 33, you are still young enough

01:14:33.292 --> 01:14:34.376
to have your...

01:14:35.834 --> 01:14:37.459
physical attributes,

01:14:37.626 --> 01:14:38.876
but old enough

01:14:38.959 --> 01:14:42.209
to no longer have them
with vanity or triumphalism.

01:14:42.292 --> 01:14:43.376
And...

01:14:44.167 --> 01:14:47.751
33 is still young enough
not to be hopelessly cynical

01:14:47.834 --> 01:14:49.584
and resigned to your fate.

01:14:51.584 --> 01:14:54.209
<i>I am discovering everything all at once.</i>

01:14:54.292 --> 01:14:55.542
<i>And the catalyst,</i>

01:14:57.084 --> 01:14:58.667
<i>the catalyst is sex.</i>

01:15:00.834 --> 01:15:04.251
I am just stupidly living

01:15:04.334 --> 01:15:05.709
now in the present.

01:15:07.876 --> 01:15:10.376
I could be fodder for
the Camorrista and not care.

01:15:17.792 --> 01:15:19.042
Someone...

01:15:20.667 --> 01:15:22.459
has opened a door to a...

01:15:23.417 --> 01:15:24.834
wet

01:15:24.917 --> 01:15:26.084
and weeping...

01:15:27.751 --> 01:15:29.376
dirty...

01:15:29.459 --> 01:15:30.501
hurricane.

01:15:32.626 --> 01:15:34.251
Look after little Sergei.

01:15:34.917 --> 01:15:36.709
He is a Russian innocent,

01:15:36.792 --> 01:15:38.667
and Russian innocents are the most innocent

01:15:38.751 --> 01:15:40.042
of innocents in the world.

01:15:42.084 --> 01:15:43.876
You should be in that car, Sergei.

01:15:44.542 --> 01:15:46.126
Keep them under control.

01:15:46.209 --> 01:15:48.709
Stop them from spending needless finances.

01:15:48.792 --> 01:15:50.834
Oh, don't worry. I'm following later.

01:15:50.917 --> 01:15:52.167
<i>Señor.</i>

01:15:52.251 --> 01:15:53.959
And they could be better off without me.

01:15:54.042 --> 01:15:57.001
Tisse is a Capuchin monk
with money, doesn't eat.

01:15:57.126 --> 01:15:59.251
And Aleksandrov is so charismatic

01:15:59.334 --> 01:16:01.376
that everyone else pays for his bed and board.

01:16:01.459 --> 01:16:03.584
He could scarcely be a drain
on anyone's resources.

01:16:04.667 --> 01:16:06.251
We need to talk.

01:16:10.376 --> 01:16:11.751
Salud!

01:16:11.834 --> 01:16:15.834
Sergei, with over 100 miles of film,

01:16:15.917 --> 01:16:19.376
you're going to make a film 20 hours long,

01:16:19.459 --> 01:16:22.042
which is stupid and intolerable.

01:16:23.459 --> 01:16:28.542
Griffith shot 200 miles on <i>Intolerance.</i>

01:16:28.626 --> 01:16:32.626
Von Stroheim shot 100 miles on <i>Greed.</i>

01:16:33.334 --> 01:16:35.126
It is normal to shoot that much,

01:16:35.209 --> 01:16:39.792
and we have a project here
covering the whole of Mexico.

01:16:42.917 --> 01:16:44.626
We are not at all doing badly,

01:16:44.709 --> 01:16:47.251
considering all the language difficulties,

01:16:47.334 --> 01:16:49.876
the extras that don't turn up
or turn up too late,

01:16:49.959 --> 01:16:52.042
the Mexican authorities who, out of the blue,

01:16:52.126 --> 01:16:54.751
when we are all prepared,
deny us permission,

01:16:54.834 --> 01:16:57.584
the exceptional heat
that is making everyone sick,

01:16:57.667 --> 01:17:00.709
then, then the heavy rains,
not known for 20 years,

01:17:00.792 --> 01:17:03.042
and then I fall sick with some mystery disease

01:17:03.126 --> 01:17:06.001
that no one can find a name for, even in Aztec.

01:17:07.167 --> 01:17:08.542
And what about this letter

01:17:08.626 --> 01:17:11.251
that Upton sent to the Russians in America,

01:17:11.334 --> 01:17:13.709
saying that the hacienda story's
the only one that makes a film

01:17:13.792 --> 01:17:15.667
that anyone could understand in Hollywood

01:17:15.751 --> 01:17:18.459
and that the rest is just
aimless pretty pictures?

01:17:19.834 --> 01:17:23.209
Upton does not simply understand

01:17:23.292 --> 01:17:27.042
that the film needs to be edited the right way.

01:17:27.126 --> 01:17:29.667
Well, he says the rushes are the same thing

01:17:29.751 --> 01:17:31.626
- over and over again.
- Jesus!

01:17:31.709 --> 01:17:33.126
That's the way you make a film, god damn it!

01:17:33.209 --> 01:17:34.417
Where have you been?

01:17:34.501 --> 01:17:36.792
We keep shooting till we get it right.

01:17:36.876 --> 01:17:40.542
Not every single retake
is in the goddamn film!

01:17:40.626 --> 01:17:42.917
He said, anyway, at the end of his letter

01:17:43.001 --> 01:17:45.084
that he was convinced that it would be

01:17:45.167 --> 01:17:47.709
a beautiful and magnificent work of art.

01:17:47.792 --> 01:17:52.334
And, and look what he wrote
to Stalin, "Dear Stalin..."

01:17:52.417 --> 01:17:55.542
You don't address the Premier
of the USSR like that.

01:17:55.626 --> 01:17:58.417
Upton did, and he's a writer.

01:17:58.501 --> 01:17:59.917
"You may have heard

01:18:00.001 --> 01:18:03.667
"that I have taken the job
of financing a moving picture,

01:18:03.751 --> 01:18:06.917
"which the Soviet director Sergei Eisenstein

01:18:07.001 --> 01:18:08.542
"is making in Mexico.

01:18:08.626 --> 01:18:12.084
"It is going to be extraordinary work

01:18:12.167 --> 01:18:15.042
"and I think will be a revelation

01:18:15.126 --> 01:18:18.167
"of the moving-picture art.

01:18:18.251 --> 01:18:20.042
"Someday you will see the picture

01:18:20.126 --> 01:18:21.626
"which Eisenstein is making

01:18:21.709 --> 01:18:23.917
"and realise that Soviet technique

01:18:24.001 --> 01:18:26.292
"has advanced another step

01:18:26.376 --> 01:18:30.376
"and been crowned with fresh laurels."

01:18:30.459 --> 01:18:32.542
Well, I'm not sure what else
he wrote in that letter,

01:18:32.626 --> 01:18:34.334
but he must have provoked Stalin somehow,

01:18:34.417 --> 01:18:36.459
because this is what he telegrammed

01:18:36.542 --> 01:18:38.584
back to your husband.

01:18:42.626 --> 01:18:45.709
"Eisenstein lose his comrade confidence
in Soviet Union.

01:18:45.792 --> 01:18:47.876
"Stop. He is thought to be a deserter

01:18:47.959 --> 01:18:49.751
"who broke off with his own country. Stop.

01:18:49.834 --> 01:18:51.084
"I'm afraid the people here

01:18:51.167 --> 01:18:52.834
"would have no interest in him. Stop.

01:18:52.917 --> 01:18:56.001
"I'm very sorry,
but all assert it is the fact. Stop.

01:18:56.084 --> 01:18:57.501
"My regards, Stalin."

01:18:57.584 --> 01:19:01.167
How did you get hold of a private telegram

01:19:01.251 --> 01:19:03.042
from Stalin to my husband?

01:19:03.126 --> 01:19:04.334
Well, from those very people

01:19:04.417 --> 01:19:06.001
who apparently have no interest in me.

01:19:06.084 --> 01:19:07.459
So who's lying?

01:19:11.167 --> 01:19:14.709
And my husband wrote back at once,

01:19:14.792 --> 01:19:18.542
saying he had never,
ever thought you were a deserter

01:19:18.626 --> 01:19:20.542
and had never been disloyal

01:19:20.626 --> 01:19:23.042
and that you were ferociously attacked

01:19:23.126 --> 01:19:25.751
by the American rednecks in California

01:19:25.834 --> 01:19:28.584
and that you stood firm in your principles

01:19:28.667 --> 01:19:30.959
and had every intention of returning

01:19:31.042 --> 01:19:32.709
when the film was completed.

01:19:32.792 --> 01:19:34.959
There are so many contradictions
flying around

01:19:35.042 --> 01:19:36.417
to your advantage,

01:19:36.501 --> 01:19:39.584
it is hard to believe
that you want us to succeed.

01:19:39.667 --> 01:19:41.792
And I wonder what you have not contributed

01:19:41.876 --> 01:19:43.667
to all these contradictions.

01:19:43.751 --> 01:19:45.251
You have been nothing but trouble

01:19:45.334 --> 01:19:46.959
from the moment we started.

01:19:47.042 --> 01:19:49.334
Even on the train leaving Los Angeles,

01:19:49.417 --> 01:19:51.042
you get into a fight with the brother

01:19:51.126 --> 01:19:52.751
of the Mexican Chief of Police.

01:19:52.834 --> 01:19:54.167
Well, we weren't to know who he was!

01:19:54.251 --> 01:19:56.209
He was ravishing some woman
on my couchette!

01:19:57.376 --> 01:20:00.667
With nights under hotel arrest
until Sinclair phoned Chaplin

01:20:00.751 --> 01:20:02.834
to persuade them to release you.

01:20:02.917 --> 01:20:04.917
Well, see how popular we are.

01:20:05.001 --> 01:20:07.292
In the end, we had 12 American senators,

01:20:07.376 --> 01:20:08.542
Douglas Fairbanks,

01:20:08.626 --> 01:20:10.709
and Albert Einstein rooting for us.

01:20:10.792 --> 01:20:13.376
And the Mexican President apologised.

01:20:13.459 --> 01:20:15.334
What about that business with the young man

01:20:15.417 --> 01:20:18.584
stealing your gun and shooting his sister?

01:20:18.667 --> 01:20:21.042
That was an unhappy accident,
which you well know.

01:20:21.126 --> 01:20:22.459
And it wasn't my gun.

01:20:22.542 --> 01:20:24.334
This troublemaker, your brother,

01:20:24.417 --> 01:20:26.001
is being very far from helpful.

01:20:26.084 --> 01:20:27.834
His poor, not to say, bad management,

01:20:27.917 --> 01:20:30.167
and his not knowing anything
about film production

01:20:30.251 --> 01:20:33.292
has wasted hundreds of dollars
that we could do well with.

01:20:33.376 --> 01:20:35.709
He has presented me to your husband

01:20:35.792 --> 01:20:38.501
as a liar and a blackmailer
and God knows what else.

01:20:38.584 --> 01:20:41.417
It is impossible to work
under such an ignorant tyrant.

01:20:41.501 --> 01:20:43.834
What the hell does he know
about film production?

01:20:43.917 --> 01:20:46.792
He's just a stockbroker salesman
from the provincial South.

01:20:46.876 --> 01:20:48.959
You have to get him off my back.

01:20:50.876 --> 01:20:53.001
- I wouldn't be at all surprised...
- <i>Señor!</i>

01:20:53.084 --> 01:20:54.542
If he was spending the film money

01:20:54.626 --> 01:20:56.459
on women, drink, and gambling.

01:20:56.542 --> 01:20:58.001
We all know he was jailed in Mérida

01:20:58.084 --> 01:20:59.542
for public indecency at a brothel,

01:20:59.626 --> 01:21:02.917
throwing whores into a... swimming pool.

01:21:03.001 --> 01:21:05.334
You are a liar and a slanderer.

01:21:05.417 --> 01:21:07.917
I am a respectable businessman,

01:21:08.001 --> 01:21:10.334
and you and your company
are just a bunch of homos.

01:21:10.417 --> 01:21:11.626
Ah, what have we provoked?

01:21:11.709 --> 01:21:13.376
I think Mary, Mrs Upton Sinclair,

01:21:13.459 --> 01:21:15.584
we have all said more than
we intended, Kimbrough?

01:21:15.667 --> 01:21:18.417
I think not, Mr Sergei Eisenstein.

01:21:18.501 --> 01:21:19.667
I think not.

01:21:19.792 --> 01:21:22.876
Well, how am I to arrive
in this skeleton state for real?

01:21:22.959 --> 01:21:24.167
You have four options.

01:21:24.459 --> 01:21:26.876
One. The Stalin option,
an assassin from Moscow.

01:21:27.159 --> 01:21:28.601
Poisoned coffee.

01:21:29.292 --> 01:21:30.709
Machete in the desert.

01:21:30.792 --> 01:21:32.926
Pig falling down from balcony.

01:21:34.209 --> 01:21:36.084
Car without brakes. Eight out of ten.

01:21:36.167 --> 01:21:38.209
Oh, or two, wasting away

01:21:38.292 --> 01:21:40.667
in a Mexican jail for moral turpitude,

01:21:40.751 --> 01:21:44.167
either for the seduction
of the young and under aged or...

01:21:44.451 --> 01:21:45.917
Or, or for sodomy,

01:21:46.001 --> 01:21:48.834
in which case expect perhaps
a red-hot poker up your arse

01:21:48.917 --> 01:21:50.417
like Edward II.

01:21:50.501 --> 01:21:51.876
Six out of ten.

01:21:51.959 --> 01:21:53.751
Or three, Sinclair's revenge.

01:21:53.834 --> 01:21:55.417
He sets light to my film.

01:21:55.501 --> 01:21:57.542
And throws you on the pyre.
Two out of ten.

01:21:57.626 --> 01:21:59.709
Or four, the Camorrista kidnap me

01:21:59.792 --> 01:22:01.251
and cut me up into little pieces,

01:22:01.334 --> 01:22:03.376
mailing me off on the slow boat
to Saint Petersburg.

01:22:03.459 --> 01:22:06.001
500,000 rubles for every pound of flesh.

01:22:06.084 --> 01:22:08.209
- Zero out of ten.
- Which is it going to be?

01:22:08.376 --> 01:22:11.251
Well, I think the Camorrista
are the most deserving.

01:22:11.334 --> 01:22:13.084
We don't want to disappoint them.

01:22:13.167 --> 01:22:15.251
We just have to take
Hunter Kimbrough's photograph

01:22:15.542 --> 01:22:16.876
and give it to the newspapers.

01:22:16.959 --> 01:22:18.101
That will do nicely.

01:22:18.751 --> 01:22:19.751
Camorrista!

01:22:22.292 --> 01:22:23.559
No! No! No!

01:23:09.417 --> 01:23:10.834
Come on, try it.

01:23:20.917 --> 01:23:23.417
Right. Come on.

01:23:24.751 --> 01:23:27.001
Right, left.

01:23:50.292 --> 01:23:51.292
Hey.

01:23:54.917 --> 01:23:58.209
Well, I have to teach from 11:00
for three hours.

01:23:59.334 --> 01:24:00.584
See you later.

01:24:53.376 --> 01:24:55.292
Pera? ls that you?

01:24:56.126 --> 01:24:59.167
<i>Sergei, it's the middle of the night.</i>

01:24:59.501 --> 01:25:01.209
Oh, I'm sorry, were you asleep?

01:25:01.292 --> 01:25:02.501
Did I wake you?

01:25:02.959 --> 01:25:04.751
Do you have anyone with you?

01:25:05.251 --> 01:25:06.876
<i>Sergei, is that likely?</i>

01:25:07.601 --> 01:25:12.584
I was wondering
if you had finally given in to Boris.

01:25:12.667 --> 01:25:16.042
<i>Things are heating up here
about your long absence.</i>

01:25:16.126 --> 01:25:18.542
<i>They are threatening
to take away your apartment.</i>

01:25:18.667 --> 01:25:20.751
What? They can't do that.

01:25:20.834 --> 01:25:22.876
<i>Sergei, I'm afraid they can.</i>

01:25:22.959 --> 01:25:25.334
<i>Do you want me to start
packing up your books?</i>

01:25:25.417 --> 01:25:27.501
<i>My God, it will take me months.</i>

01:25:27.584 --> 01:25:29.334
Listen, Pera, listen,

01:25:29.417 --> 01:25:34.251
I have something extraordinary
to tell you.

01:25:34.334 --> 01:25:36.584
This country...
This country is astonishing.

01:25:36.667 --> 01:25:39.417
All the large things in life
constantly hit you on your head,

01:25:39.501 --> 01:25:41.834
in the pit of your stomach,
and in your heart.

01:25:42.042 --> 01:25:43.834
Nothing can be superficial.

01:25:45.584 --> 01:25:46.751
You know how I work...

01:25:46.834 --> 01:25:49.334
Timid with affairs
of the heart and body.

01:25:49.417 --> 01:25:52.751
My prick always safely tucked up
in my trousers.

01:25:52.834 --> 01:25:54.126
<i>Sergei!</i>

01:25:54.209 --> 01:25:55.751
You know I'm a work automaton.

01:25:55.834 --> 01:25:58.709
Well, suddenly my timidity collapsed.

01:25:59.626 --> 01:26:01.042
My defences fell down.

01:26:03.084 --> 01:26:06.417
I shocked myself.
I behaved without reserve.

01:26:06.501 --> 01:26:08.876
You would have been
both shocked and amazed.

01:26:08.959 --> 01:26:10.626
And I would have wanted you to be.

01:26:12.667 --> 01:26:15.709
Everything we ever talked about
has been bowled over.

01:26:17.309 --> 01:26:19.209
I have been moaning
and complaining to you

01:26:19.292 --> 01:26:20.626
that I could not go the distance.

01:26:20.709 --> 01:26:22.009
Well, now I have...

01:26:23.542 --> 01:26:25.542
And beyond.

01:26:27.584 --> 01:26:29.667
I have got everything
that I desired.

01:26:30.709 --> 01:26:32.792
And not just
the satisfaction of lechery.

01:26:33.084 --> 01:26:36.167
<i>Sergei, your secrets are safe with me.</i>

01:26:36.251 --> 01:26:38.917
<i>And you can tell me everything
later in every detail,</i>

01:26:39.001 --> 01:26:40.959
<i>but you must be careful.</i>

01:26:41.042 --> 01:26:43.417
<i>Now, hold your excitement
and tell me things</i>

01:26:43.501 --> 01:26:45.292
<i>our listener might want to hear.</i>

01:26:45.792 --> 01:26:50.209
Pera, I am sure
there is no secret listener.

01:26:51.417 --> 01:26:54.126
It is you, Pera,
you are the secret listener.

01:26:54.209 --> 01:26:55.376
You are two people.

01:26:55.459 --> 01:26:57.667
<i>Sergei, you might be right.</i>

01:26:57.751 --> 01:27:00.001
<i>I have probably
always been two people...</i>

01:27:00.084 --> 01:27:03.084
<i>Your secretary, nurse, and bum-wiper.</i>

01:27:06.251 --> 01:27:09.917
Pera, you have never wiped my backside,

01:27:10.001 --> 01:27:11.667
but Cañedo...

01:27:11.751 --> 01:27:13.209
<i>But Cañedo has?</i>

01:27:13.834 --> 01:27:15.667
<i>Sergei, shut up!</i>

01:27:15.751 --> 01:27:19.167
Pera, you are the only person
in the world

01:27:19.251 --> 01:27:23.042
that I can tell
without holding anything back.

01:27:23.126 --> 01:27:27.126
<i>That is both the best and the worst thing
you can tell me,</i>

01:27:27.209 --> 01:27:30.959
<i>especially on a cold October morning
at five degrees below zero.</i>

01:27:32.126 --> 01:27:35.584
<i>Now that I know you are well
and happy and working hard,</i>

01:27:35.667 --> 01:27:37.459
<i>I wait for your next call.</i>

01:27:38.709 --> 01:27:41.126
<i>I'm now going to cry myself to sleep.</i>

01:27:41.501 --> 01:27:42.751
<i>Good night, Sergei.</i>

01:27:43.209 --> 01:27:45.001
<i>Take very good care of yourself.</i>

01:28:36.501 --> 01:28:37.626
Death...

01:28:38.542 --> 01:28:41.876
Should always be ready
to take a call.

01:29:09.292 --> 01:29:12.084
Found you, Eisenstein.
Is this filmmaking?

01:29:12.209 --> 01:29:13.459
Of a kind.

01:29:13.834 --> 01:29:15.626
Looking after your feet is important.

01:29:16.417 --> 01:29:20.042
Did you know that ignoring
your feet in old age

01:29:20.126 --> 01:29:22.001
statistically brings on death?

01:29:22.084 --> 01:29:24.251
Corns, chilblains, blisters.

01:29:24.667 --> 01:29:26.834
In-growing toenails
cause walking problems.

01:29:26.917 --> 01:29:28.834
Problems of balance create falls,

01:29:28.917 --> 01:29:31.084
which mean damaged hips,
broken bones,

01:29:31.167 --> 01:29:32.626
which don't mend so good after 60.

01:29:32.709 --> 01:29:34.001
How old are you, Mr Kimbrough?

01:29:34.084 --> 01:29:36.709
Eisenstein, I have a chiropodist

01:29:36.792 --> 01:29:38.126
to tell me all that.

01:29:38.209 --> 01:29:40.084
Oh, another mark of American affluence.

01:29:40.167 --> 01:29:43.542
Your average Russian wouldn't know
what a chiropodist was.

01:29:43.626 --> 01:29:45.417
So look after your feet, Kimbrough.

01:29:45.751 --> 01:29:47.542
If not, collapse of mobility,

01:29:47.626 --> 01:29:51.542
a downhill slide to permanent horizontality
without sex.

01:29:51.959 --> 01:29:55.292
Pneumonia, bedsores, depression, death.

01:29:55.834 --> 01:29:57.792
Stay vertical as long
as you can, Kimbrough.

01:29:57.876 --> 01:30:00.417
Look after your shoes
and look after your feet.

01:30:00.501 --> 01:30:02.876
Upton has sent me with an ultimatum.

01:30:03.417 --> 01:30:06.209
You have 20 days left
on your visa, Mr Eisenstein.

01:30:10.126 --> 01:30:11.126
God, Kimbrough!

01:30:11.209 --> 01:30:13.417
Have you brought along
the Mexican Passport Office?

01:30:13.501 --> 01:30:15.709
I'm afraid you'll have
to leave Mexico, sir.

01:30:15.792 --> 01:30:18.667
In that time, you have enough raw stock
to finish the film

01:30:18.751 --> 01:30:20.501
and a budget of $8,000.

01:30:20.584 --> 01:30:23.001
That's 20 minutes a day for 20 days.

01:30:23.417 --> 01:30:24.709
Enough is enough.

01:30:24.792 --> 01:30:26.792
We have to bring this thing to an end.

01:30:26.876 --> 01:30:27.876
"This thing?"

01:30:27.959 --> 01:30:31.001
What to you, Mr Kimbrough,
is "this thing"?

01:30:31.084 --> 01:30:35.167
A long, protracted, irresponsible adventure

01:30:35.251 --> 01:30:36.584
leading to nowhere.

01:30:36.667 --> 01:30:38.917
Mary says Upton has to tame

01:30:39.001 --> 01:30:41.167
your disobedience and extravagance.

01:30:41.251 --> 01:30:44.751
Upton has collapsed and is sick
in hospital in Pasadena.

01:30:44.834 --> 01:30:47.209
The doctors say
too much unnecessary stress.

01:30:47.292 --> 01:30:49.292
He's been running around
on your behalf,

01:30:49.376 --> 01:30:52.834
forever raising money to satisfy
your exorbitant demands.

01:30:54.001 --> 01:30:55.751
I now take over.

01:30:56.334 --> 01:30:59.917
Upton has lost his faith in you
and your integrity.

01:31:01.459 --> 01:31:04.417
You have manoeuvred him, used him.

01:31:05.209 --> 01:31:07.751
He has empowered me to close it down,

01:31:07.834 --> 01:31:10.709
wrap it up, the end, full stop.

01:31:12.001 --> 01:31:13.751
You're like a Negro.

01:31:13.834 --> 01:31:16.959
Kind words and consideration
are not enough.

01:31:20.292 --> 01:31:22.084
I thought I was a Red.

01:31:23.084 --> 01:31:24.584
Now I'm also a Black?

01:31:25.167 --> 01:31:26.959
And you also forgot, a Jew.

01:31:27.292 --> 01:31:30.542
Being Russian is the mildest of concerns.

01:31:31.209 --> 01:31:35.459
You wear your prejudices
proudly on your sleeve, Mr Kimbrough,

01:31:35.542 --> 01:31:37.334
a true Southern gentleman.

01:31:37.501 --> 01:31:40.292
Upton is exhausted by your hesitations

01:31:40.376 --> 01:31:42.626
and delays and changes of plan

01:31:42.709 --> 01:31:45.042
and the dubious company you keep.

01:31:45.376 --> 01:31:47.709
You have deliberately
packed filth in our luggage

01:31:47.792 --> 01:31:50.542
sent through
United States Customs Authorities.

01:31:50.626 --> 01:31:53.376
The police said it was the
vilest thing they'd ever seen...

01:31:53.459 --> 01:31:56.459
Obscene and blasphemous drawings
of the Crucifixion.

01:31:56.542 --> 01:31:58.584
I leave for Hollywood on Wednesday.

01:31:59.084 --> 01:32:02.251
The last of the rushes
have to be in by the 21st of December

01:32:02.334 --> 01:32:03.834
when the contract terminates.

01:32:04.917 --> 01:32:06.876
Amkino and Moscow

01:32:06.959 --> 01:32:09.376
have said you must return to New York.

01:32:11.126 --> 01:32:14.126
You sail from New York
on the 17th of January.

01:32:15.084 --> 01:32:18.251
You'll be arriving in Europe
by the 23rd.

01:32:18.626 --> 01:32:20.334
Perhaps you can be back in Moscow

01:32:20.417 --> 01:32:22.042
by the 2nd of February.

01:32:23.167 --> 01:32:25.792
You miss the connection,
you are on your own.

01:32:25.876 --> 01:32:28.876
Mr Cañedo is no longer
your guide here in Guanajuato.

01:32:29.251 --> 01:32:30.459
He has been dismissed.

01:32:30.626 --> 01:32:31.667
Mr Cañedo,

01:32:31.751 --> 01:32:34.292
in Mexico City, they talked
about ending your contract

01:32:34.376 --> 01:32:36.001
at the end of this period.

01:32:36.084 --> 01:32:37.834
It's best for his sake, Eisenstein,

01:32:37.917 --> 01:32:40.084
you should leave Guanajuato immediately.

01:32:40.167 --> 01:32:41.959
He has a wife and children.

01:32:42.042 --> 01:32:43.751
I suggest tomorrow morning!

01:32:45.292 --> 01:32:46.584
<i>Allí, cabrón.</i>

01:32:46.667 --> 01:32:48.459
<i>Quieto, cabrón, hijo de la chingada.</i>

01:35:10.334 --> 01:35:11.709
All right, Sergei.

01:35:12.251 --> 01:35:14.959
Now you have to give them back.

01:35:45.126 --> 01:35:47.042
What were you thinking of doing,

01:35:47.126 --> 01:35:49.292
opening a restaurant in Red Square?

01:35:50.917 --> 01:35:52.709
Don't you have forks in Moscow?

01:35:54.667 --> 01:35:56.459
It was my insurance policy...

01:35:58.709 --> 01:36:00.876
An excuse to be arrested.

01:36:27.542 --> 01:36:28.584
There.

01:36:29.459 --> 01:36:30.959
Now I cannot leave Guanajuato.

01:36:32.001 --> 01:36:34.001
I cannot go home.

01:36:35.959 --> 01:36:38.167
You must never separate
a Russian from his shoes.

01:36:40.167 --> 01:36:41.584
I cannot leave you.

01:36:42.667 --> 01:36:44.709
I cannot.

01:38:08.917 --> 01:38:10.667
Palomino loves well.

01:38:29.167 --> 01:38:30.417
You were lonely.

01:38:33.501 --> 01:38:35.001
You needed comforting.

01:38:38.167 --> 01:38:39.751
You were like a lost child.

01:38:55.834 --> 01:38:57.126
I love him.

01:39:06.501 --> 01:39:07.959
I love him, too.

01:39:50.376 --> 01:39:52.792
We will come to say good-bye.

01:39:55.084 --> 01:39:56.292
We want peace...

01:39:57.542 --> 01:39:58.667
All of us.

01:40:00.417 --> 01:40:03.126
And I am the one
to seal that peace.

01:40:04.959 --> 01:40:07.126
You have to go now, Sergei.

01:40:07.917 --> 01:40:09.209
Your time is up.

01:40:11.417 --> 01:40:12.917
We want Palomino back.

01:40:15.084 --> 01:40:18.292
He is not gonna spend
his time dreaming of Moscow.

01:40:31.417 --> 01:40:32.501
Drive away.

01:40:34.709 --> 01:40:36.792
This is the Day of the Dead,

01:40:36.876 --> 01:40:39.876
and I am a dead man.

01:40:42.251 --> 01:40:44.334
Drive slowly to the edge of town.

01:40:44.792 --> 01:40:46.417
This is a funeral cortege.

01:40:48.667 --> 01:40:51.084
And when you reach the edge of town,

01:40:51.876 --> 01:40:53.709
drive like the Devil.

01:40:53.792 --> 01:40:56.209
I need to leave Heaven in a hurry.

01:41:10.084 --> 01:41:14.251
<i>Eisenstein left Mexico
two months later.</i>

01:41:15.626 --> 01:41:19.709
<i>He had shot some 250 miles of film,</i>

01:41:19.792 --> 01:41:23.459
<i>which he was never allowed to edit.</i>

01:41:23.542 --> 01:41:30.042
<i>Soviet laws made homosexuality
a punishable offence in 1936.</i>

01:41:30.126 --> 01:41:33.334
<i>Homosexuals were sent to Siberia.</i>

01:41:33.417 --> 01:41:37.167
<i>Ten years' hard labour for sodomy.</i>

01:41:37.251 --> 01:41:42.667
<i>Eisenstein dies of heart attack
aged 50 in 1948,</i>

01:41:42.751 --> 01:41:46.292
<i>banging on the radiator pipes
for over three hours</i>

01:41:46.376 --> 01:41:48.376
<i>to arouse his neighbours,</i>

01:41:48.459 --> 01:41:50.542
<i>a prearranged signal,</i>

01:41:50.626 --> 01:41:53.084
<i>but they never heard him.</i>

01:41:55.584 --> 01:41:58.917
Day ten of my stay in Guanajuato

01:42:00.376 --> 01:42:02.292
is the 31st of October

01:42:03.126 --> 01:42:04.459
and the eve

01:42:05.417 --> 01:42:07.209
of the Day of the Dead.

01:42:09.292 --> 01:42:11.709
In the West, my film <i>October</i> is called

01:42:13.334 --> 01:42:15.417
<i>The Ten Days That Shook The World.</i>

01:42:16.417 --> 01:42:17.626
I...

01:42:18.709 --> 01:42:20.834
shall consider these ten days

01:42:21.584 --> 01:42:24.292
as the ten days that shook...

